  "chapter": {
    "number": 5,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Eliphaz Continues: God Blesses those Who Seek Him"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Call out if you please, but who will answer?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "To which of the holy ones will you turn?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For resentment kills a fool,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and envy slays the simple.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I have seen a fool taking root,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but suddenly his house was cursed.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "His sons are far from safety,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "crushed in court without a defender.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The hungry consume his harvest,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "taking it even from the thorns,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and the thirsty pant after his wealth.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3153
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For distress does not spring from the dust,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and trouble does not sprout from the ground.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Yet man is born to trouble",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "as surely as sparks fly upward.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "However, if I were you, I would appeal to God",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and lay my cause before Him—",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "the One who does great and unsearchable things,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "wonders without number.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He gives rain to the earth",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and sends water upon the fields.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He sets the lowly on high,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so that mourners are lifted to safety.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He thwarts the schemes of the crafty,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so that their hands find no success.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He catches the wise in their craftiness,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3154
          },
          {
            "text": "and sweeps away the plans of the cunning.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They encounter darkness by day",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and grope at noon as in the night.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He saves the needy from the sword in their mouth",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and from the clutches of the powerful.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "So the poor have hope,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and injustice shuts its mouth.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Blessed indeed is the man whom God corrects;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so do not despise the discipline of the Almighty.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3155
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For He wounds, but He also binds;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He strikes, but His hands also heal.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He will rescue you from six calamities;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "no harm will touch you in seven.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "In famine He will redeem you from death,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and in battle from the stroke of the sword.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You will be hidden from the scourge of the tongue,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and will not fear havoc when it comes.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You will laugh at destruction and famine,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and need not fear the beasts of the earth.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For you will have a covenant with the stones of the field,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the wild animals will be at peace with you.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You will know that your tent is secure,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and find nothing amiss when inspecting your home.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You will know that your offspring will be many,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "your descendants like the grass of the earth.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You will come to the grave in full vigor,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like a sheaf of grain gathered in season.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 27,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Indeed, we have investigated, and it is true!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "So hear it and know for yourself.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
